          <LEXSenses>
            <LEXSense LanguageCode="en" LastEdited="2021-02-04 21:40:49" LastEditedBy="">
              <DefinitionLong/>
              <DefinitionShort>(an idiom, literally: to throw fire) to cause discord and contention</DefinitionShort>
              <Glosses>
                <Gloss>to cause discord</Gloss>
                <Gloss>to cause division</Gloss>
              </Glosses>
              <Comments>Some translators have preferred to retain the literal rendering of this expression in {S:04201204900006}, since this seems to be necessary in view of the larger figurative context, which speaks of ‘how I wish it were already kindled’ (τί θέλω εἰ ἤδη ἀνήφθη). A strictly literal translation may, however, be understood in a completely physical sense, namely, ‘to set the world on fire.’ There are a number of quite diverse interpretations of the significance of this expression in {S:04201204900006}. Some have assumed, for example, that it refers to the fire of Pentecost.</Comments>
            </LEXSense>
          </LEXSenses>
